ODM leader Raila Odinga has had a busy schedule since he travelled to India with his wife Ida on Friday. Raila has visited Bangalore State, where he celebrated the enduring legacy of his father and former Vice President Jaramogi Oginga Odinga. “I met Kenyan students in Bangalore and reflected on Mzee Jaramogi’s days in the city decades ago. I encouraged them to work hard and remain focused,” Raila said on Twitter yesterday. He has met Gamini Perera, an MP and Cabinet Minister in the government of the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka. He has attended a wedding reception in Bangalore, where he met Senator Tan Sri Dato, President of the Upper House in Malaysia’s Parliament, and Bookanakere Yeddurappa, who is former Chief Minister of India’s state of Karnataka. Click here for
the latest political news